message.content:
This command uses the Secure Shell (SSH) protocol to connect to an Amazon Web Services (AWS) EC2 instance with a private key located at "~/UserKey.pem". It also sets up port forwarding from your local machine's port 25900 to the remote server's port 5900.

The -C flag enables compression, which can improve performance over slow connections. The -L flag specifies that connections to the specified local TCP port or Unix socket file will be forwarded over the secure channel, and the input on the destination port will be forwarded back to the source workstation.
